bbox": [104.2, 387.9, 1168.3, 411.2]}, {"text": "flows associated with servicing the residential mortgage loans. This calculation uses a number of assumptions that", "bbox": [104.2, 412.9, 1163.3, 436.2]}, {"text": "are based on current market conditions. The range and weighted-average of the significant unobservable inputs", "bbox": [104.2, 437.9, 1137.9, 461.2]}, {"text": "used to fair value our residential mortgage servicing assets at December 31, 2018, along with the valuation", "bbox": [104.2, 462.9, 1094.3, 486.2]}, {"text": "techniques, are shown in the following table:", "bbox": [104.2, 487.9, 512.9, 511.2]}, {"text": "December 31, 2018", "bbox": [699.9, 531.3, 831.2, 547.6]}, {"text": "December 31, 2017", "bbox": [972.8, 531.3, 1104.1, 547.6]}, {"text": "Valuation Technique", "bbox": [110.4, 569.6, 251.1, 585.9]}, {"text": "Significant", "bbox": [463.8, 555.0, 538.3, 571.3]}, {"text": "Unobservable Input", "bbox": [432.9, 569.6, 569.1, 585.9]}, {"text": "Range", "bbox": [879.8, 555.0, 924.4, 571.3]}, {"text": "(Weighted-Average)", "bbox": [833.5, 569.6, 970.5, 585.9]}, {"text": "Discounted cash flow", "bbox": [110.4, 593.8, 248.2, 610.1]}, {"text": "Prepayment speed", "bbox": [375.0, 593.8, 497.4, 610.1]}, {"text": "8.45 - 56.11% (9.08%)", "bbox": [746.5, 593.8, 892.0, 610.1]}, {"text": "9.16 - 51.52% (10.46%)", "bbox": [1010.5, 593.8, 1164.5, 610.1]}, {"text": "Discount rate", "bbox": [375.0, 616.7, 460.9, 633.0]}, {"text": "7.50 - 10.00% (7.54%)", "bbox": [745.7, 616.7, 891.6, 633.0]}, {"text": "8.50 - 11.00% (8.54%)", "bbox": [1019.7, 616.7, 1165.1, 633.0]}, {"text": "Servicing cost", "bbox": [375.0, 639.6, 465.8, 655.9]}, {"text": "$62 - $5,125 ($68.25)", "bbox": [751.4, 639.6, 891.6, 655.9]}, {"text": "$76 - $4,385 ($83.11)", "bbox": [1025.3, 639.6, 1164.5, 655.9]}, {"text": "If these economic assumptions change or prove incorrect, the fair value of residential mortgage servicing assets", "bbox": [104.2, 690.0, 1140.5, 713.3]}, {"text": "may also change. Prepayment speed, discount rates, and servicing cost  are critical to the valuation of residential", "bbox": [104.2, 715.0, 1150.9, 738.3]}, {"text": "mortgage servicing assets. Estimates of these assumptions are based on how a market participant would view the", "bbox": [104.2, 740.0, 1160.2, 763.3]}, {"text": "respective rates and reflect historical data associated with the residential mortgage loans, industry trends, and other", "bbox": [104.2, 765.0, 1175.2, 788.3]}, {"text": "considerations. Actual rates may differ from those estimated due to changes in a variety of economic factors. An", "bbox": [104.2, 790.0, 1139.0, 813.3]}, {"text": "increase in the prepayment speed would cause a negative impact on the fair value of our residential mortgage", "bbox": [104.2, 815.0, 1122.0, 838.3]}, {"text": "servicing assets. An increase in the assigned discount rates and servicing cost assumptions would cause a", "bbox": [104.2, 840.0, 1094.2, 863.3]}, {"text": "decrease in the fair value of our residential mortgage servicing assets.", "bbox": [104.2, 865.0, 750.3, 888.3]}, {"text": "The amortization of residential mortgage servicing assets for December 31, 2018, as shown in the table above, is", "bbox": [104.2, 915.0, 1152.1, 938.3]}, {"text": "recorded as a reduction to contractual fee income. The contractual fee income from servicing residential mortgage", "bbox": [104.2, 940.0, 1159.8, 963.3]}, {"text": "loans totaled $14 million for the year ended December 31, 2018. This fee income was offset by $4 million of", "bbox": [104.2, 965.0, 1099.3, 988.3]}, {"text": "amortization for the year ended December 31, 2018. Both the contractual fee income and the amortization are", "bbox": [104.2, 990.0, 1122.1, 1013.3]}, {"text": "recorded, net, in “mortgage servicing fees” on the income statement.", "bbox": [104.2, 1015.0, 735.2, 1038.3]}, {"text": "10. Premises and Equipment", "bbox": [467.3, 1066.2, 807.7, 1094.2]}, {"text": "Premises and equipment at December 31, 2018, and 